# Data pipelines (Iceberg ingestion)

Rules that apply when working on the discovery → director → materialise
→ verify → annotate pipeline. See [docs/data-catalog.md](mdc:docs/data-catalog.md)
for the prose walkthrough and [docs/flows.md#1-generic-file--iceberg-ingestion](mdc:docs/flows.md)
for the canonical sequence diagram.

## Pipeline contract

The five stages are pinned to specific files and dataclasses:

| Stage | File | Output |
| --- | --- | --- |
| Discover | [aqp/data/pipelines/discovery.py](mdc:aqp/data/pipelines/discovery.py) | `list[DiscoveredDataset]` |
| Plan | [aqp/data/pipelines/director.py](mdc:aqp/data/pipelines/director.py) | `IngestionPlan` |
| Materialise | [aqp/data/pipelines/materialize.py](mdc:aqp/data/pipelines/materialize.py) | `MaterializeResult` |
| Verify | [aqp/data/pipelines/director.py](mdc:aqp/data/pipelines/director.py) (`verify_after_materialise`) | `VerifierVerdict` |
| Annotate | [aqp/data/pipelines/annotate.py](mdc:aqp/data/pipelines/annotate.py) | `AnnotationResult` |

The orchestrator [`IngestionPipeline`](mdc:aqp/data/pipelines/runner.py)
sequences them; aggregate output is `IngestionReport`.

## Hard rules

1. Iceberg writes go through `iceberg_catalog.append_arrow` (and
   `create_or_replace_table`). Never call PyIceberg's
   `Catalog.create_table` / `Table.append` directly.
2. The Director is a Nemotron LLM call by default
   (`AQP_LLM_DIRECTOR_MODEL=nemotron-3-nano:30b`). It must always
   produce an `IngestionPlan` — when the LLM is unreachable / returns
   garbage / is disabled, fall back to the deterministic
   `_identity_plan` in
   [aqp/data/pipelines/director.py](mdc:aqp/data/pipelines/director.py).
3. The Director's JSON parser
   (`_parse_director_response`) must handle reasoning-style output
   that prefixes the JSON with chain-of-thought. It walks every
   balanced `{...}` block longest-first and accepts the first one
   containing the required top-level key.
4. The verifier triggers when
   `rows_written < expected_min_rows / 2` OR every file was skipped.
   It returns `accept` or `retry` — retries are capped at one per
   dataset.
5. Discovery groups members by `_family_key(subdir, leaf_name)`
   so SEC-style sibling subdirs keep distinct family keys when their
   leaf names collide.
6. Browser-style `(N)` duplicate suffixes collapse via
   `_dedup_key` + `outer_mtime`; the most recently modified file
   wins, the rest are recorded under `inventory_extra` with
   `reason="duplicate-suffix-suppressed"`.
7. USPTO-style `.xml` archives go to the synthetic `__assets__`
   family with an explanatory note. Don't try to ingest them as
   tabular data unless you've written a streaming XML extractor.

## Iceberg namespaces

Use the `aqp_<source>` slug pattern. The four regulatory namespaces
are reserved:

- `aqp_cfpb`
- `aqp_uspto`
- `aqp_fda`
- `aqp_sec`

`aqp` is the default fallback; `aqp_smoke` is reserved for
[scripts/iceberg_smoke.py](mdc:scripts/iceberg_smoke.py). Pick a new
`aqp_<source>` slug for any new corpus.

## Tests

- [tests/data/test_discovery_patches.py](mdc:tests/data/test_discovery_patches.py)
  covers discovery edge cases (subdir disambig, XML, duplicates).
- [tests/data/test_director.py](mdc:tests/data/test_director.py)
  covers director planning + verifier; stub `_call_llm` with
  `monkeypatch` to keep tests hermetic.
- [tests/data/test_pipelines_smoke.py](mdc:tests/data/test_pipelines_smoke.py)
  is the end-to-end smoke; pass `director_enabled=False` to
  `IngestionPipeline` so the LLM path is bypassed.

## Don't

- Don't lower the discovery's tabular ext set without updating the
  XML / non-tabular tests.
- Don't bypass the Director by calling `materialize_dataset`
  directly from a route or task — go through `IngestionPipeline`.
- Don't widen the Director's prompt without checking it still fits
  in the model's context (4K token output budget by default).
- Don't store director_raw beyond 32KB in the report — truncate.
- Don't add a per-source Celery task; use
  `ingest_local_paths_with_director` or spawn one
  `_run_one_source.py` subprocess per path
  (see [scripts/ingest_regulatory.py](mdc:scripts/ingest_regulatory.py)).
